Review comment:
       Because `Subtract` call we go through asserts Arg0 and Arg1 to be equal to T:
   ```
     template <typename T, typename Arg0, typename Arg1>
     static constexpr enable_if_signed_integer_value<T> Call(KernelContext*, Arg0 left,
                                                             Arg1 right, Status*) {
       static_assert(std::is_same<T, Arg0>::value && std::is_same<T, Arg1>::value, "");
       return arrow::internal::SafeSignedSubtract(left, right);
     }
   ```
   Similar holds for date32. We could make `enable_if_signed_integer_value` accept Arg0 and T and make `enable_if_heterogeneous_signed_integer_value` to cover casting cases.




